The paper focuses on analyzing smartphone usage data to infer cognitive impairment, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of structured models and machine learning techniques to analyze the data suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The interpretability of the model and the insights gained from the analysis suggest a focus on social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of data analysis and modeling techniques suggests a focus on computational methods (cs.CY).
